Fortune Hunter
Educational dungeon crawler with magic and monsters
Attack monsters by completing 4th grade math questions such as arithmetic, geometry, and pattern recognition
Developed through the Humanitarian Open Source Development course
One Laptop Per Child
One Laptop Per Child is a UN program aimed at providing affordable laptops to developing nations as a way to bolster their education programs.
In countries such as Paraguay, every school aged child has their own laptop that they use to complete class assignments.

Teaches 4th grade math and economic concepts such as decimals and money
Uses the Fortune Hunter game engine
Developed through the Humanitarian Open Source Development course
